---
title: Çilbir (Turkish Eggs)
source: Ottolenghi
servings: 2
tags:
  - turkish
  - eggs
  - breakfast
  - vegetarian
---

In a #small saucepan{}, melt @butter{3%tbsp} over medium heat. Add @Aleppo pepper{1%tsp}
(or @red pepper flakes{1/2%tsp} as substitute). Cook for ~{1%minute} until butter
is infused and slightly foamy. Set aside.

Mix @Greek yogurt{1%cup}(full-fat, room temperature) with @garlic{1%clove}(finely grated)
and @salt{1/4%tsp} in a #bowl{}.

Bring a #saucepan{} of water to a gentle simmer. Add @white vinegar{1%tbsp}.

Poach @eggs{4} for ~poach{3%minutes} until whites are set but yolks are still runny.

> Strain each egg through a fine-mesh sieve first to remove wispy whites —
> this gives you much neater poached eggs.

Divide the yogurt between 2 plates, creating a well in the center.

Place 2 poached eggs on each plate. Drizzle with the Aleppo butter.

Sprinkle with @fresh dill{1%tbsp}(chopped) and @sumac{1/2%tsp}.

Serve immediately with @crusty bread{} for dipping.
